The paper deals with explaining the outcomes of a ranking algorithm used in a news recommendation system. This involves techniques from information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG), as well as natural language processing (CL) and artificial intelligence (AI) to develop the LISTEN and Q-LISTEN models. Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the models in a real-world user study, which involves human-computer interaction (HC). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.HC.
